{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Build a complete Shopify theme (Dawn-based or custom) as a single-product landing page store. This is a high-conversion shapewear/body care product page. Output all required Liquid, CSS, and JS files.
    
    ## STORE STRUCTURE
    - Homepage = product landing page (single product, selectable via theme settings)
    - No collection pages, no catalog — one product only
    - Product selectable in Customizer: settings_schema.json → product picker field
    
    ## SECTIONS REQUIRED (in order)
    
    ### 1. HERO SECTION
    - Full-width product image (Shopify CDN, lazy loaded)
    - Headline (bold, luxury serif — e.g. Cormorant Garamond or Playfair Display)
    - Subheadline (light weight sans-serif)
    - Primary CTA: "Add to Cart" button → triggers AJAX cart
    - Optional: countdown timer (customizable end date via metafield or setting)
    - Customizer fields: headline, subheadline, image, CTA text, show/hide countdown
    
    ### 2. BENEFITS / FEATURES GRID
    - 3–6 icon + title + description cards
    - Asymmetric layout (NOT identical 3-column AI grid — vary sizes, one featured card full-width)
    - Icons: SVG inline (no colored circles)
    - Customizer: each card editable (icon, title, body)
    
    ### 3. PRODUCT DETAILS + ADD TO CART (sticky on scroll)
    - Variant selector (size/color)
    - Quantity picker
    - Add to Cart button (large, high contrast)
    - Price with compare-at (sale badge if applicable)
    - Sticky ATC bar on mobile (fixed bottom)
    - AJAX cart → slide-out drawer (no page reload)
    
    ### 4. TRUST BADGES
    - Free Shipping | Secure Checkout | 30-Day Money-Back Guarantee | Made in EU (customizable)
    - Icons inline SVG
    - Horizontal row, responsive stacked on mobile
    
    ### 5. SOCIAL PROOF / REVIEWS
    - Star rating aggregate (schema.org markup)
    - 3–5 testimonial cards (photo, name, verified badge, review text)
    - Customizer: each review editable
    - Optional: Okendo or Judge.me widget placeholder (commented toggle)
    
    ### 6. FAQ ACCORDION
    - 5 default questions (customizable in Customizer)
    - Smooth CSS animation expand/collapse
    - Schema.org FAQPage markup for SEO
    
    ### 7. FOOTER
    - Minimal: logo, links (Privacy, Refund, Terms), payment icons (Visa, MC, PayPal, Klarna)
    - GDPR cookie consent banner (lightweight, no external lib)
    
    ---
    
    ## TRACKING EVENTS — FULL IMPLEMENTATION
    
    ### Meta Pixel (Facebook/Instagram)
    Inject via theme.liquid head. Pixel ID configurable in theme settings.
    
    Events to fire:
    - PageView → on every page load
    - ViewContent → on product section entering viewport (Intersection Observer)
    - AddToCart → on ATC button click (include content_ids, value, currency, content_type)
    - InitiateCheckout → on checkout button click
    - Purchase → on order status page (via additional_checkout_scripts)
    
    ```liquid
    {% if settings.meta_pixel_id != blank %}
    <!-- Meta Pixel -->
    <script>
    !function(f,b,e,v,n,t,s){...}(window,document,'script','https://connect.facebook.net/en_US/fbevents.js');
    fbq('init','{{ settings.meta_pixel_id }}');
    fbq('track','PageView');
    </script>
    <noscript><img height="1" width="1" style="display:none" src="https://www.facebook.com/tr?id={{ settings.meta_pixel_id }}&ev=PageView&noscript=1"/></noscript>
    {% endif %}
    ```
    
    ### TikTok Pixel
    Same pattern. TikTok Pixel ID configurable in theme settings.
    
    Events to fire:
    - PageView → on load
    - ViewContent → Intersection Observer on product section
    - AddToCart → on ATC click (include content_id, value, currency, quantity)
    - InitiateCheckout → on checkout click
    - CompletePayment → on order status page
    
    ```liquid
    {% if settings.tiktok_pixel_id != blank %}
    <script>
    !function(w,d,t){...}(window,document,'script');
    ttq.load('{{ settings.tiktok_pixel_id }}');
    ttq.page();
    </script>
    {% endif %}
    ```
    
    ### Google Analytics 4
    GA4 Measurement ID configurable in settings.
    
    Events:
    - page_view → automatic
    - view_item → on ViewContent trigger
    - add_to_cart → on ATC click
    - begin_checkout → on checkout click
    - purchase → on order status page
    
    ### Unified Event Handler (JS)
    Create `assets/tracking.js`:
    - Single `fireEvent(eventName, data)` function
    - Dispatches to all active pixels simultaneously
    - Reads pixel IDs from `window.themeSettings` object injected via Liquid
    - Debounced to avoid duplicate fires
    
    ---
    
